Under the theme "Music Must Go On," the ongoing Beijing Music Festival is holding 10 concerts for its Music at Noon section until October 20, which aims to entertain people as they enjoy their lunch breaks.  The BMF Lunch Time Concert Series will feature live performances that will also be aired on Beijing Music Radio and through major Chinese streaming sites as well as the BMF's own app. The Wednesday concert Yaya and Friends was staged by Jaya Sun, Gao Can and Zhu Mu with a playlist that included Saint Saens' Introduction and Rondo Capriccioso in A minor. Op. 28 and The Carnival of the Animals and Jacques Offenbach's Les Larmes de Jacqueline.  
